Seyffert wrongly insists on taking these abla- tives (which are ablatives absolute) as ablatives of measure after cudi· candoe sunt ‘by the strengthening and steadying of the mind and life'. Had Cic. meant this he would have written corroborandis. But how can it be said that advancing years supply a measure or standard sor judging about friendships?
